column1: This table is field data collected in the upper reaches of the V40 stream in the former Karamea Mine near Denniston, New Zealand.
This data set was created by Eric Barefoot by pacing along streams and taking wetted stream width measurements every ~5 meters with a tape measure.
This data was collected to determine the distribution of stream widths in headwater catchments.
Measurement interval was demarcated with length of rope ~5 meters long.
GPS waypoints were taken at nodes in the stream network.

column2: Internal and external stream segments usually seperated by nodes. Order is arbitrary
We either paced upstream or downstream
Raw width measurements taken in inches
Estimated percentage of the streams that were not flowing due to sandbars, rocks, vegetation, or other material at the surface of the stream
